Ways to connect to a remote repo

Git clone
1-git clone <remote-url>

Examples:

HTTPS → git clone https://github.com/user/repo.git

SSH → git clone git@github.com:user/repo.git

GitHub CLI → gh repo clone user/repo

2= Add a Remote to an Existing Local Repo

git remote add origin <remote-url>


Examples:

HTTPS → git remote add origin https://github.com/user/repo.git

SSH → git remote add origin git@github.com:user/repo.git

3- Fork + Clone (Special GitHub / GitLab flow)

Fork a repo on GitHub/GitLab.

Clone your fork:

git clone https://github.com/your-username/repo.git


Add the original repo as upstream:

git remote add upstream https://github.com/original-owner/repo.git

4 - Generate an SSH Key (if not already)

ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -C "your_email@example.com"


Default location:

Private key → ~/.ssh/id_rsa

Public key → ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub

Add SSH Key to Agent

eval "$(ssh-agent -s)"
ssh-add ~/.ssh/id_rsa


Copy Public Key to Remote Hosting Service

cat ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub


Copy the output and paste into:

GitHub → Settings > SSH and GPG Keys > New SSH Key

GitLab → Settings > SSH Keys

Bitbucket → Personal Settings > SSH Keys

                        
                            Git environment 
                🌍 Remote Repository (e.g., GitHub, GitLab)
                ──────────────────────────────────────────
                          |             ^
   git push               |             |    git pull
   (upload commits)       |             |    (fetch + merge)
                          v             |
                ──────────────────────────────────────────
                🖥️ Local Repository
                ──────────────────────────────────────────
                       |     ↑
   git checkout        |     |   git fetch
   (switch branch)     |     |   (download commits but
                       v     |    do not merge yet)
                ──────────────────────────────────────────
                Working Directory (your files)
                ──────────────────────────────────────────
                       | 
   git add             |
   (stage changes)     |
                       v
                ──────────────────────────────────────────
                Staging Area (Index)
                ──────────────────────────────────────────
                       |
   git commit          |
   (save snapshot)     v
                ──────────────────────────────────────────
                Local Repository (Commits History)
                ──────────────────────────────────────────






